===Etymology===
Greek for "same sound"
===Noun===
#a word which is pronounced the same as another word but differs in spelling and meaning.
#:'''Note''' This term is distinct from [[homonym]] which is correctly applied only to words that are identically spelled but have different meanings, usually based on distinct etymologies.
#a letter or group of letters which are pronounced the same as another letter or group of letters.
===Examples===
[[carat]], [[caret]], [[carrot]], [[karat]]

